  "prompt": "How can I livestream to Facebook using a DSLR camera?",
  "response": "To livestream to Facebook using a DSLR camera, you'll need:\n\n1. Hardware requirements:\n- DSLR camera with clean HDMI output\n- HDMI capture device/card\n- Computer\n- Stable internet connection\n\n2. Software options:\n- OBS Studio (free)\n- Xsplit\n- Wirecast\n- Facebook Live streaming app\n\n3. Steps:\na) Connect your DSLR to capture device\nb) Connect capture device to computer via USB\nc) Configure OBS or chosen streaming software\nd) Set up Facebook Live streaming settings\ne) Select your camera as video source\nf) Choose streaming quality and bitrate\ng) Click \"Go Live\" on Facebook\n\n4. Additional tips:\n- Use camera's AC adapter for continuous power\n- Set camera to manual mode\n- Use a tripod for stability\n- Check audio levels\n- Ensure good lighting\n- Have a strong, stable internet connection\n\n5. Recommended capture devices:\n- Elgato Game Capture HD60 S\n- AVerMedia Live Gamer Portable\n- Razer Ripsaw HD\n\nEach setup might require slight variations, so consult your specific camera and capture device manuals.",
